40|$|The Ouchterlony double {{diffusion}} {{method in}} agar gel {{has been used}} to study the antigens of the vaccinia and <b>pig</b> <b>pox</b> viruses and their corresponding antibodies. The existence of a common antigenic constituent in the two viruses has been demonstrated. The sensitivity of the method was found to be adequate for sera giving complement fixation titres of 1 / 80. The complications arising from the presence of antibodies to heterologous (host) antigens are illustrated...|$|E
